To implement monthly and yearly something like this:
```
const y = new Date(Date.UTC(2020,0))
    , m = new Date(y)

const start = {
  year: (d) => {
    y.setUTCFullYear(d.getUTCFullYear())
    return y.getTime()
  }, 
  month: (d) => {
    m.setUTCFullYear(d.getUTCFullYear())
    m.setUTCMonth(d.getUTCMonth())
    return m.getTime()
  }
}

p(new Date(start.month(new Date(2022, 6))))
```

or calculate the incrementing periods as durations for each cycle



const first = {
  year: x => (x.setMonth(0), x.setDate(1), x),
  month: x => (x.setDate(1), x),
  week: x => (x.setDate(x.getDate() - t.daysMap[wkst][x.getDay()]), x)
}
